        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:56PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 755 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Red Bay, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40-50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Bay, Atwood, Duketon, Rockwood, Vina, Halltown, Pleasant Site,
Belgreen, Dempsey, and Isbell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northwestern Alabama.</instruction>
